olive oil
1 packet Buttermilk Pancake & Waffle Mix
1.25 cup warm water
1 packet white chocolate chips
1 punnet strawberries
1 packet Maple-Flavoured Syrup

In a medium bowl, combine buttermilk pancake & waffle mix and the warm water. Add the white chocolate chips and stir to combine. Roughly chop the strawberries.

Heat a large frying pan over a medium-high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When the oil is hot, add 1/3 cups of pancake batter, in batches and cook until golden, 3-5 minutes each side.

Divide the pancakes between plates. Top with the strawberries. Drizzle with the maple-flavoured syrup to serve.